It looks like your Interactive Robot UI was "messed up" because of a color contrast conflict between the white robot body and the light grey/white background, as well as some minor issues with how the interactive layers (UI vs. 3D) were stacked.

I have optimized the code to align with the Rahix AI branding.

Key Fixes Made:
High Contrast Background: Switched the background to a deeper Slate-950 gradient (Rahix Dark Mode) so the white robot body and green glowing eyes "pop" properly.

UI Layer Visibility: Fixed the text containers to use backdrop-blur and a darker glass effect so instructions are readable.

Interaction Refinement: Corrected the Raycaster logic to ensure clicking the robot's body feels more responsive.

Premium Aesthetic: Added a subtle pulsing glow to the robot's yellow "power core" and green eyes to match a "Premium" display mode.

HTML

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Rahix AI | Interactive Assistant</title>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; overflow: hidden; }

