**PROMPT FOR VIBE CODE AI: Interactive 3D Robot Mascot with Eye-Tracking**

Create a standalone, interactive 3D robot character built entirely with CSS and vanilla JavaScript. The robot's eyes follow the user's cursor in real-time, and the head tilts with a parallax effect based on mouse position.

---

## **ROBOT SPECIFICATIONS**

### **Container Structure:**

```html
<div class="robot-wrapper" id="robot">
  <div class="speech-bubble">Hi I'm Rahi!</div>

  <div class="robot">
    <!-- Robot Head -->
    <div class="robot-head">
      <div class="robot-face">
        <div class="eyes-container">
          <div class="eye">
            <div class="glow"></div>
            <div class="pupil" id="leftPupil"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="eye">
            <div class="glow"></div>
            <div class="pupil" id="rightPupil"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Robot Body -->
    <div class="robot-body">
      <div class="robot-chest"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Arms -->
    <div class="robot-arm arm-left"></div>
    <div class="robot-arm arm-right"></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

## **CSS STYLING**

### **Robot Wrapper (Container):**
```css
.robot-wrapper {
  position: relative;
  width: 400px;
  height: 500px;
  animation: robotFloat 4s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes robotFloat {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0px); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-20px); }
}

.robot {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}
```

---

### **Robot Head:**
```css
.robot-head {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 200px;
  height: 180px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0f0f5 0%, #d0d0e0 100%);
  border-radius: 50% 50% 45% 45%;
  box-shadow: 
    0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.3),
    inset 0 -10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1),
    inset 0 10px 20px rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
  z-index: 20;
}
```

---

### **Face Screen:**
```css
.robot-face {
  position: absolute;
  top: 60px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 160px;
  height: 100px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #0f0f1e 100%);
  border-radius: 30px;
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
  border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
}
```

---

### **Eyes Container:**
```css
.eyes-container {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  display: flex;
  gap: 30px;
}

.eye {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  background: #000;
  border-radius: 50%;
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(100, 200, 255, 0.5);
}

.eye::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00d4ff 0%, #0099ff 100%);
  border-radius: 50%;
  opacity: 0.8;
}
```

---

### **Pupils (Interactive Part):**
```css
.pupil {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  background: #000;
  border-radius: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  transition: transform 0.1s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94);
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.8);
}

.pupil::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 3px;
  right: 3px;
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  background: white;
  border-radius: 50%;
}
```

---

### **Eye Glow Effect:**
```css
.glow {
  position: absolute;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.8) 0%, transparent 70%);
  opacity: 0.5;
  animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 0.3; transform: scale(1); }
  50% { opacity: 0.6; transform: scale(1.2); }
}
```

---

### **Robot Body:**
```css
.robot-body {
  position: absolute;
  top: 220px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 160px;
  height: 200px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e0e0f0 0%, #c0c0d0 100%);
  border-radius: 40px;
  box-shadow: 
    0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.2),
    inset 0 -10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}

.robot-chest {
  position: absolute;
  top: 40px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 100px;
  height: 80px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.4), rgba(255,255,255,0.1));
  border-radius: 20px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
}
```

---

### **Robot Arms:**
```css
.robot-arm {
  position: absolute;
  top: 240px;
  width: 60px;
  height: 120px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d0d0e0 0%, #b0b0c0 100%);
  border-radius: 30px;
}

.arm-left {
  left: 60px;
  transform: rotate(20deg);
}

.arm-right {
  right: 60px;
  transform: rotate(-20deg);
}
```

---

### **Speech Bubble:**
```css
.speech-bubble {
  position: absolute;
  top: 20px;
  right: 20px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  color: #333;
  padding: 12px 20px;
  border-radius: 20px;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  opacity: 0;
  transform: scale(0.8) translateY(10px);
  animation: popIn 0.5s 1s forwards, floatBubble 3s ease-in-out infinite 1s;
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

@keyframes popIn {
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1) translateY(0);
  }
}

@keyframes floatBubble {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-5px); }
}

.speech-bubble::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -10px;
  left: 20px;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  border-left: 10px solid transparent;
  border-right: 10px solid transparent;
  border-top: 10px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
}
```

---

## **JAVASCRIPT - EYE TRACKING (CRITICAL)**

```javascript
// Real-time cursor tracking for robot eyes
document.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
  const leftPupil = document.getElementById('leftPupil');
  const rightPupil = document.getElementById('rightPupil');
  const robot = document.getElementById('robot');

  if (!leftPupil || !rightPupil || !robot) return;

  // Get robot's position on screen
  const robotRect = robot.getBoundingClientRect();
  const robotCenterX = robotRect.left + robotRect.width / 2;
  const robotCenterY = robotRect.top + robotRect.height / 2;

  // Calculate angle between robot and cursor
  const angle = Math.atan2(
    e.clientY - robotCenterY, 
    e.clientX - robotCenterX
  );

  // Calculate distance (max 10px pupil movement)
  const distance = Math.min(
    10, 
    Math.hypot(e.clientX - robotCenterX, e.clientY - robotCenterY) / 20
  );

  // Calculate pupil offset coordinates
  const offsetX = Math.cos(angle) * distance;
  const offsetY = Math.sin(angle) * distance;

  // Apply transform to pupils (instant reaction, no delay)
  leftPupil.style.transform = 
    `translate(calc(-50% + ${offsetX}px), calc(-50% + ${offsetY}px))`;
  rightPupil.style.transform = 
    `translate(calc(-50% + ${offsetX}px), calc(-50% + ${offsetY}px))`;

  // Subtle head tilt based on cursor position (parallax effect)
  const tiltX = (e.clientX - window.innerWidth / 2) / 50;
  const tiltY = (e.clientY - window.innerHeight / 2) / 50;

  robot.style.transform = 
    `perspective(1000px) rotateY(${tiltX}deg) rotateX(${-tiltY}deg)`;
});

// Touch device support
document.addEventListener('touchmove', (e) => {
  if (e.touches.length > 0) {
    const touch = e.touches[0];
    const mouseEvent = new MouseEvent('mousemove', {
      clientX: touch.clientX,
      clientY: touch.clientY
    });
    document.dispatchEvent(mouseEvent);
  }
});
```

---

## **KEY FEATURES**

1. **Eye Tracking:** Pupils follow cursor with instant response (no smoothing delay)
2. **3D Head Tilt:** Robot head tilts based on cursor position (parallax effect)
3. **Floating Animation:** Gentle up/down bob (4s loop, 20px movement)
4. **Speech Bubble:** Pops in after 1s, floats gently
5. **Eye Glow:** Pulsing cyan glow effect on eyes
6. **Touch Support:** Works on mobile devices

---

## **USAGE**

Place this robot component anywhere on your page. It's completely self-contained and will track the cursor automatically. Adjust the `.robot-wrapper` width/height to scale the entire robot proportionally.

**Responsive:** For mobile, reduce container size:
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .robot-wrapper {
    width: 300px;
    height: 400px;
  }
}
```

---

**RESULT: A fully functional, interactive 3D robot mascot with real-time eye-tracking and parallax head movement!*

